sub_title: Senior Associate Consultant @ PwC | Org Transformation | ESG
summary:
A hands-on problem-solver, who gets excited turning ideas into reality, and re-imagining organizations strategies and products to tackle world's complex puzzles. My studies in Mathematical Economics, and Strategy & Organization, combined with my international work and study experience in the Netherlands, U.S., Czech Republic, and Bulgaria allow me to approach problems with a multifaceted perspective, creativity and an analytical mind. I bring strong communication skills, conceptual thinking and positive attitude and curiosity in all my work, and my purpose is to contributing to an economically, socially, and environmentally prosperous world.

I love getting inspiration, and some topics that intrigue me are:
Consultancy | Sustainable Innovation | ESG | Design Thinking | New Org Models | Agile | Digital Transformation | UX Design | Gamification | Web 3 | XR | AI | Shared Economy | Neuropsychology | Psychology | Behavioral science
